OL,3,CMan pleads guilty to sending
OL,4,C'abhorrent' messages to Jess Carter
OL,6,F"In this case, Dewale sent hateful and
OL,7,Fmalicious messages, thinking that he
OL,8,Fwould be able to hide behind his
OL,9,Faccount name.
OL,11,F"His comments were totally abhorrent,
OL,12,Fthey caused emotional distress for
OL,13,FMiss Carter and her family and I
OL,14,Fwelcome the guilty plea entered today.
OL,16,F"We have been clear that hate crime
OL,17,Fonline or in person, is not acceptable
OL,18,Fand as we have shown in this case, you
OL,19,Fcannot hide behind a social media
OL,20,Fprofile to post vile comments and
OL,21,Fspread hate."
